<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10578] Groovydoc noscripts and nomainforscripts options no longer work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10578</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Groovydoc used to support the &lt;tt&gt;noscripts&lt;/tt&gt; option to not include scripts, and &lt;tt&gt;nomainforscripts&lt;/tt&gt; to exclude the script&apos;s main method from the documentation. As of Groovy 3, these options no longer work, because they were only part of the old parser, and never added to the new one. They should either be removed from the documentation and API, or reimplemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reproduction:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Make a Script.groovy&lt;br/&gt;
2. Run &lt;tt&gt;groovydoc -noscripts --destdir=doc . Script.groovy&lt;/tt&gt; under Groovy 2&lt;br/&gt;
3. Notice that the Script class is NOT in the docs.&lt;br/&gt;
4. Run &lt;tt&gt;groovydoc -noscripts --destdir=doc . Script.groovy&lt;/tt&gt; under Groovy 3 or 4.&lt;br/&gt;
5. Notice that the Script class is now in the docs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A similar set of steps can be used for &lt;tt&gt;nomainforscripts&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Linux, Java 11, Groovy 3.0.10 and 4.0.2.</environment>
